						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up on the bund of Achchanna tank.</p>						

						<p>Annadēva-mahārāja, A.D. [1436?].</p>						

						<p>[Undated, but likely of the inscription of the same chief noticed in No. 296- A.R. No. 64 of 1956-57. This inscription was noted in <hi rend="italic">NDI</hi> as a continuation of the inscription noticed as A.R. No. 64 of 1956-57].</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of the temple of Gōpīnātha in the name of Annadēvarāja, and a tank in the name of his mother, Lakshmīdēvi by Potarāju Mantrirāja (See N.D.I. Part I, p. 302).</p>						

						</summary>
